{
  "texts": [
    "Panel B shows results for Rust versus Haskell, where we find a similar pattern.",
    "While both innovation types see enhanced effects from the model improvement, the absolute increase remains larger for maintenance activities.",
    "Overall, both these findings suggest that as LLMs improve their ability to understand and interpret the context, their differential impact on innovation types persists and potentially widens, rather than narrowing the gap.",
    "The absolute effect increases for both code development and maintenance activities, but the enhancement is greater for maintenance tasks.",
    "This pattern aligns with our expectation that improved contextual understanding particularly benefits tasks with well-defined solution spaces and rich available context."
  ]
}